.readonly-field {
    background: #f3f3f3 !important;
    cursor: not-allowed;
}


✅ STEP 1 — Put form mode in a helpful variable

At the top of your popup:

@{
    bool isNew = Model.RebuiltId == 0;
}


So now you can use:

.Enable(isNew)


or

HtmlAttributes(new { @readonly = !isNew ? "readonly" : null })

✅ STEP 2 — Make ALL normal inputs read-only in edit mode

Use this pattern for every EditorFor:

@Html.EditorFor(m => m.RebuiltId, new {
    htmlAttributes = new {
        @class = "k-textbox",
        style = "width:100%",
        @readonly = !isNew ? "readonly" : null
    }
})


Same idea applies to all standard HTML textbox fields.
